NAME

    Book::BestOfCPAN - Because the CPAN is huge


DESCRIPTION

        "CPAN is the language, Perl is just its syntax" -- Audrey Tang

    This book is written with the hope to help people who wonder which of
    the numerous modules available on the CPAN will answer the problems they
    have (and maybe event the problems they will have).


INSTALLATION

    To install this module, run the following commands:

        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install

    Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the
    following commands:

        perl Build.PL
        ./Build
        ./Build test
        ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

    After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
    perldoc command.

        perldoc Book::BestOfCPAN

    You can also look for information at:

        RT, CPAN's request tracker
            http://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Dist=Book-BestOfCPAN

        AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
            http://annocpan.org/dist/Book-BestOfCPAN

        CPAN Ratings
            http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Book-BestOfCPAN

        Search CPAN
            http://search.cpan.org/dist/Book-BestOfCPAN


